node.text:
In order to stretch our capacities and grow as humans, we are required to do things we haven’t yet done.

Imposter syndrome is something we all feel when we’re pushing these boundaries and treading into not-yet-known territory. Everyone feels this same thing. When you realize this, you won’t have any reason left to stop yourself. 

#impostersyndrome #personalgrowth #trusttheprocess

🎥 by @maxwmccoy
🎶 "Remember Jah" by the incredible @satsang

node.title: How To Push Past Self-Imposed Boundaries

node.text:
This past trimester in @fit.for.service we have been training to cultivate the full expression of the sacred masculine. Our journey through the Austin summit started with a poetry workshop by the great @inqlife where we learned to alchemize our grievances into gratitude through the medium of spoken word. We entered workshops where we explored the complicated nuances of the psyche, and prepared ourselves to retrain the harsh inner critic into a loving and supportive inner coach. 

To test what we had been learning, we created the Elemental Games. Five teams were charged with representing the five Earth elements with costume and dance, and then offered the opportunity to represent their team in competition. It was one of the most powerful ceremonies any of us have ever been a part of. Before the paint washed off, we came together with a deeper appreciation for every single person who entered the arena. 

We enjoyed a stunning private concert with @satsang, a night of sober celebration, and one of the most potent speeches I have ever heard by the philosopher king Charles Eisenstein. 

I’m so grateful to everyone who participated in Trimester 2. And as my teacher Don Howard always said, there is always another layer. We’ll go together to find that layer this October in Sedona for Trimester 3. If you are interested in applying, click the link in bio or head to aubreymarcus.com/fitforservice

🎥 by @maxwmccoy

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Aubrey Marcus in Costa Rica. May be an image of one or more people and text that says 'Aubre Marcus @AubreyMarcus The rarest gift you can give, is Love. Love you no matter what, just as you are, and you are always forgiven. expect nothing and am grateful for everything. give you the truth only and always. You are learning in the perfect way." Give this gift to yourself first'.

node.text:
There are a lot of ways we try to show Love. There are even books written about “love languages”. But Love in its raw and wild form needs no translation. It just is. 

Give Love and you give the gift of a king or queen, at the price any pauper can pay.

#love #lovequotes #selflove

The future IS bored holding on to all of your expectations and judgments of what "should" be. Let go of the baggage. We don't need it where we're going'.

node.text:
The lighter you travel, the more enjoyable the journey. And nothing is more effervescent than the present moment. 🤍

#bepresent #letgoofthepast #presence

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Aubrey Marcus in Costa Rica. May be an image of 1 person and text that says '"WHEN WE ARE NO LONGER ABLE TO CHANGE A SITUATION- WE ARE CHALLENGED TO CHANGE DURSELVES." -VIKTOR E. FRANKL'.

node.text:
There is no better example of a situation we cannot change, than one that happened in the past. But nonetheless we will ruminate on whatever it is, as if we had a time machine in our pocket. Nothing in the past can change. But your response to everything that happened in the past is up to you. Will you allow it to make you stronger? Will you forgive yourself? Can you be grateful, no matter how hard it was? It’s all a choice. And making that choice is how you change yourself, right now in the present moment.

Artist: Anatheme 

#changequotes #acceptance #changeyourlife

node.text:
Eleven years ago, I first sat in ceremony with ayahuasca shaman Maestro Orlando Chujandama of the Quechua lineage.

I spoke about my journey on #JRE127. It was the most profound ayahuasca experience of my life. Until yesterday. 

Where once again, a decade later, I am back with “El Dragon De La Selva”. It was the most profoundly difficult experience of my life. And equally as liberating.

The thing about healing is that it is a process, not a destination. 

This bothers some people. We like to think of ourselves like a machine. If we fix something once, we expect it to be fixed forever. But we are as fractal and multi-dimensional as the medicine itself.

We will accumulate more ‘sickness’ that can be cleaned, and we will discover deeper layers we haven’t yet touched.

The idea of a destination is misleading. Because there is only the journey, and the choices we make as to how we want to walk the path.

Ayahuasca is not a necessary practice. But it is a part of my way, and I’m forever grateful for everything she has offered me 💚

Art by Luis Tamani

*I’ve had a few questions about how to get in touch to work with Maestro Orlando. Here is his site: https://mushuk-pakarina.negocio.site/

The boy is friendly, the man is a friend. The boy answers, the man questions. The boy likes, the man loves. The boy hopes, the man trusts. The boy is theatrical, the man is magical. The boy tries the man does. 9:53 PM 8/13/21 Twitter Web App'.

node.text:
I may have some gray hairs in my beard, but I still got a lot of boy in me. 🤷

And that’s all good, because above all the man accepts himself. 

Also “boy” and “man” are just ways to express the idea of maturity. Don’t be distracted by the gender or associations with the words🤎

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Aubrey Marcus in Austin, Texas. May be an image of one or more people and text that says 'Aubrey Marcus @AubreyMarcus Commitment is the end of questioning. It is go until you fail, fix it until it is unfixable, with your shield or on it. Commitment is scary. But the gift of commitment is that when you are committed, there is no torturous anxiety about what you should do.'.

node.text:
It's not always easy for me to commit. 

If I give myself an out, often times I will take it. But the best things in my life have come from my deepest commitments.

So what would you like to commit to?

#committed #stayfocused #commitment

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Aubrey Marcus in Austin, Texas. May be an image of text that says 'Shame Can Only Survive In The Shadow of Silence What are you ashamed of? What do you judge yourself for? Find someone you can share your truth with, and liberate yourself. You don't need to carry the burden of your secrets. Are you ready to be be free?'.

node.text:
During a guided meditation with a powerful healer, my mind conjured up the image of Jesus. He asked me why I was sad. I explained to him all of my fears, my feelings of not doing enough, all of the ways in which I could be better. He put his hand lovingly on my head, and said the most powerful words he could say. "Me too."

Everything you are experiencing, we are all experiencing. Maybe you have it a little more or less than I do, but I promise when I look inside myself I can find the same thing as you. When you realize this, no matter what someone tells you, you won't flinch. Give yourself this gift of freedom. And be the sanctuary for all of your friends and family to liberate themselves as well. 

#shame #judgement #forgiveness
